<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFC06A7FFF8D9E6A1DA9B22B" pageId="59" pageNumber="817" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC06A7FFF8D9E6A1DA9B22B" blockId="59.[111,1320,2060,2376]" pageId="59" pageNumber="817">
Phylogenetic relationship of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC06A7FFDFB9E6A1C8FB366" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[519,655,2099,2132]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Mimetillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="817" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Mimetillus</taxonomicName>
to other genera of Vespertilioniniis still uncertain. As currently recognized, there may be multiple species included within 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC06A7FFB499E021EA4B391" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1891" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Mimetillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="59" pageNumber="817" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="moloneyi">M. moloneyi</taxonomicName>
and subspecies thomasi has been recognized as a distinct species on morphological grounds. Race berneri has been treated also as a synonym of thomas. However, a full revision of the validity of the recognized subspecies is pending and only a single species is recognized tentatively. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
